 TONGA – The driver in an alleged hit-and-run which cost the life of a police officer, has been arrested. According to police spokesman Brig Leonard Hlathi, the incident occurred on July 13. The policeman and his wife, who is also a police sergeant, were jogging when Mduduzi Ndlovu (23) knocked him over by a vehicle. Read more here: Wife gets 12 years behind bars for conspiracy to murder her husband In a bizarre twist, it was revealed that the vehicle Ndlovu had been driving in, belonged to the deceased’s wife. “How Ndlovu got possession of the vehicle remains a subject of a wide police investigation.” Ndlovu was hiding from the police until September 28 when he finally handed himself over. He appeared in the Tonga Magistrate’s Court on Monday and was remanded in custody. He will appear in the same court on October 12. https://lowvelder.co.za/371649/lowvelder-story-tip-off/